{"lemma":"عُرُنٌ","slug":"عُرُنٌ","root":"ع.ر.ن","root_slug":"ع-ر-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28857","n28858","n28859"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"den","examples":[{"text":"كَانَ الأَسَدُ نَائِمًا فِي عَرِينِهِ","english":"The lion was sleeping in his den."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thicket"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.riːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28857","headword_ar":"عِرْنٌ","root":"Ern","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, latter half:       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EironapN","text_ar":"عِرْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28858","headword_ar":"عَرَنٌ","root":"Ern","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A callousness in the hind leg of a horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar beast, above the pastern, in the hinder part thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uqaAq","text_ar":"شُقَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: and, as ISk says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purulent pustules"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroH","text_ar":"قَرْح"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that arise in the neck of a camel, in consequence of which he scratches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scrapes, himself, and sometimes he lies down against the stem of a tree and scratches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scrapes, himself therewith; and its cure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"he says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the burning of fat upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eruption like pustules,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purulent pustules, in the necks of young weaned camels, in consequence of which they scratch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scrape, themselves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB, TA:) or, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuronapN","text_ar":"عُرْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraAnN","text_ar":"عِرَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain disease in the hinder part of the hind leg of a horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like an abrasion in the skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"causing the hair to fall off:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cracking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chapping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incident to horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in their fore legs and their hind legs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a callousness that arises in the pastern of a horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar beast, and in the place of its fetlock, in the hinder part, and a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uqaAq","text_ar":"شُقَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that betides it from the kicking against a mountain or stone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul smell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foulness"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of the hands]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the smell, of flesh-meat and its grease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gamarN","text_ar":"غَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajidu raAy^iHapa Earani yadayoka","text_ar":"اَجِدُ رَايِحَةَ عَرَنِ يَدَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I perceive the odour of the foulness of thy hands with the smell of flesh-meat and its grease"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaranN","text_ar":"عَرَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odour of flesh-meat that has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earom","text_ar":"عَرْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravy"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earom","text_ar":"عَرْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"q. v.]. (TA.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odour of cooked flesh-meat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EironN","text_ar":"عِرْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relic,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of broth upon the hand of the cater."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Hejeree, TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cooked flesh-meat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh-meat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in an absolute sense. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Smoke."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of tree, with which one tans."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Dioscorides asserts the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ern","text_ar":"عرن"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plant having leaves resembling those of the small lentil, except that they are longer than they, and having a stem about a span tall, and a red flower, and a small root; growing in neglected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uncultivated, places: a poultice of its leaves with olive-oil is sudorific; its bruised leaves applied as a poultice act as a discutient to wounds and inflamed pustules; and taken in a beverage."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sirup, they cure the dribbling of the urine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Avicenna, i. e. Ibn-Seenà book ii. p. 235.)"}],"source_refs":["S","IB","TA","K","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n28859","headword_ar":"عَرِنٌ","root":"Ern","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"the masc. epithet applied to a horse, or similar beast, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having the disease termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earan","text_ar":"عَرَن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (TA:) the fem. epithet having this meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarinapN","text_ar":"عَرِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; with which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruwnN","text_ar":"عَرُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. (K, TA.)       -A2-  Also One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who keeps close to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAsir","text_ar":"يَاسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughterer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superintendent of the slaughtering and of the division, of the camel for the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that he may eat of the slaughtered camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}